\newlabel{fig:price_measurement}{{6}{21}{Effect of price measurement on inference (pre-COVID, 2010--2019). (a) Mean elasticity by price measure. (b) Percentage of specifications significant at p$<$0.05. GNI\% yields 100\% significant EaP results vs.\ \PctPPPSigEaP \% for PPP (at p$<$0.05), validating income-relative pricing as the appropriate affordability metric}{figure.6}{}}
